        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## pKa Values for Oxalic Acid (Ethanedioic Acid)\n\nOxalic acid (H₂C₂O₄) is a **diprotic acid** with **two dissociation steps**:\n\n1. **H₂L ⇌ HL⁻ + H⁺** (first dissociation)\n2. **HL⁻ ⇌ L²⁻ + H⁺** (second dissociation)\n\nThe SRD-46 database reports the following pKa values at **25 °C** and **I = 0.1 M**:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | VLM ID |\n|------|-------------|-----|--------|\n| 1 | H₂L → HL⁻ + H⁺ | **−1.2** | vlm_151532 |\n| 2 | HL⁻ → L²⁻ + H⁺ | **3.8** | vlm_151494 |",
